Git safety rules:

Before suggesting a commit:

- List ALL changed files
- Explain each change
- Identify risks

DO NOT:
- Delete large sets of files
- Modify unrelated parts of the repo
- Create destructive changes without warning

Always prefer reversible changes.

After completing any task:

- Summarize all changes
- List modified files
- Identify risks
- Generate a commit message

Do NOT wait for the user to ask.